<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=636&amp;p=5311#p5311"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[CHR extracting - when can(not) it be done?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=636&amp;p=5311#p5311"><![CDATA[
Megaman uses the UNROM board, it uses a RAM chip for CHR.  So all the CHR data is in the PRG.  If it's uncompressed you could use a normal tile editor to view the rom and find them, but if it's stored with compression it'd be a little trickier to extract it.<br /><br />If nothing else, you could use an emulator like NESten that lets you dump the $0000-$1FFF CHR region, that'll give you a copy of the tiles that are loaded currently.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sun Oct 09, 2005 2:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
